Key Match Events: Jack Leiter allowed three runs over five-plus innings, striking out a career-high six batters.
Josh Smith had a go-ahead two-run single.
Rangers reliever Andrew Chafin allowed an inherited runner to score.
Pre-Game Insights: Bochy said pregame that being with the team and watching the games would help bring a sense of comfort to Leiter.
Post-Match Reflections: Jack Leiter expressed the importance of executing each pitch and controlling adrenaline.
Josh Smith praised Leiter for keeping the team in the game and giving them a chance to win.
Leiter noted that being with the big league club has allowed him to get into a new routine and focus on learning.
